/dashboard/admin/offers              → admin queue
/buy/[registration]                  → public enquiry / viewing / doc request forms
```

Listing workspace **Leads & Offers** tab remains a **per-listing summary** linking into lead/offer detail pages — not the primary CRM surface.

## Lead detail workspace (`/dashboard/seller/leads/[leadId]`)

Layout sections:

1. **Header** — buyer, aircraft (registration + title), status badge, priority, assignee
2. **Timeline** — `LeadActivity` feed (newest first)
3. **Buyer panel** — verification / FICA status, prior enquiries on other aircraft
4. **Aircraft panel** — listing status, link to `/dashboard/listings/[listingId]`
5. **Actions** (server actions, not client-only):
   - Mark contacted
   - Qualify / unqualify (with reason)
   - Schedule viewing
   - Grant / deny document access (compliance gate)
   - Convert to offer
   - Add internal note
   - Set follow-up (`nextFollowUpAt`)
   - Close lead (`closedReason` required)

## Offer detail workspace (`/dashboard/seller/offers/[offerId]`)

Must support:

- Offer thread / negotiation history via `OfferActivity`
- Counter-offer flow → `SELLER_COUNTERED`
- Expiry → `EXPIRED` (scheduled job or checked on read)
- Accept / reject with mandatory `rejectedReason`
- **Accept** → create `Deal`, link lead to `OFFER_MADE` → `CLOSED`, open deal room
- Compare multiple active offers on same listing (side-by-side panel)

## Buyer qualification gates (aviation-specific)

| Gate | Allowed actions |
|------|-----------------|
| Unverified | General enquiry only |
| FICA pending | Enquiry + viewing request |
| FICA cleared | Document access (after grant), formal offer |

Document access:

- Private by default
- Grant creates activity + optional `ComplianceCheck`
- Short-lived signed URLs only after authorization
- Log who granted access and when

## Pipeline views (after detail pages work)

Add grouped views — status columns or filtered tabs:

- **Lead pipeline**: New → Contacted → Qualified → Viewing → Offer made → Closed
- **Offer pipeline**: Received → Under review → Countered → Accepted / Rejected / Expired
- **My follow-ups**: `nextFollowUpAt` due today / overdue
- **Admin unassigned queue**: new leads needing assignment

Status changes via action menu first; drag-and-drop is deferred.

## Dashboard integration

Feed real data into existing seller home sections:

- **Action required** — stale leads, overdue follow-ups, offers awaiting response
- **Buyer activity** — from `LeadActivity` / new offers, not mock selectors
- **Summary stats** — open leads, active offers from DB counts

Replace `buildLeadTableRows` / mock selectors incrementally; keep selector shape where possible.

## Public ingestion (`/buy/[registration]`)

Forms create persisted leads:

- Enquire (general)
- Request viewing
- Request document access (auth + verification check)

Each submission: `Lead` + `LeadActivity` + `NotificationEvent` to seller.

Offers on fixed-price listings: authenticated buyer, FICA gate, creates `Offer` + activity.

## Notifications (Phase 2+)

`NotificationEvent` for: new lead, viewing confirmed, doc access granted, counter-offer, offer accepted.

Link to `/dashboard/seller/messages` thread per lead when messages module exists.

## Analytics (defer until persistence works)

Track: `LeadCreated`, `LeadQualified`, `LeadConverted`, `OfferReceived`, `OfferAccepted`.

Seller metrics: lead → qualified → offer → deal conversion, median first-response time.

## Recommended build order

Implement in this sequence. **Do not skip activity logging or server authorization.**

```text
Phase 1 — Foundation
  [x] Prisma: Lead, Offer, LeadActivity, OfferActivity (+ indexes)
  [x] Domain enums + status meta + transition validators
  [x] Server actions with role checks
  [x] Seed or migrate mock data shape to DB

Phase 2 — Lead CRM workspace
  [x] /dashboard/seller/leads/[leadId] page
  [x] Activity timeline component (reuse listing workspace activity patterns)
  [x] Lead action sidebar (status transitions + notes + follow-up)
  [x] Wire seller/admin lead tables to DB; row links to detail page

Phase 3 — Offer negotiation workspace
  [ ] /dashboard/seller/offers/[offerId] page
  [ ] Counter / accept / reject flows
  [ ] Accept → Deal creation + deal room link
  [ ] Compare offers on same listing

Phase 4 — Ingestion & gates
  [ ] Public enquiry forms on /buy/[registration]
  [ ] FICA / verification gates on actions
  [ ] Document access grant workflow

Phase 5 — Pipeline & ops
  [ ] Follow-up queue + action required from DB
  [ ] Pipeline/grouped views
  [ ] Admin assign + qualify workflows
  [ ] Notifications

Phase 6 — Analytics
  [ ] Dashboard KPIs + PostHog events
```

When the user says **"build the leads CRM"** or **"start Phase 1"**, begin at the first unchecked phase unless they specify otherwise.

## Definition of done (CRM vs CRUD)

The feature is CRM-ready when:

1. Seller opens a **lead detail page**, sees **activity history**, takes an **action**, status changes with **audit trail**
2. **Follow-ups** appear on dashboard without hunting tables
3. **Qualification** gates document access and offers
4. **Offer accept** auto-creates a **deal**
5. Admin can **assign, review, and intervene** without raw row editing

## UI conventions

- Use shadcn `Table` for queues, `Card` + `Tabs` for detail workspaces
- Status badges use domain meta (`getLeadStatusMeta`, `getOfferStatusMeta`) — no vague "Pending"
- Row primary action: link to **lead/offer detail**, not only listing workspace
- No `section` tags in dashboard (site `globals.css` applies `py-24` to sections)
- Mock layer (`src/lib/aviatonly/mock/`) is for UI dev only — new features read/write Prisma

